As a Web Developer at Amilia, you will contribute to creating, optimizing, and maintaining our platform features. You will participate in the analysis, design, implementation, and testing of new feature development. If what you're looking for is a growing company with more than 30 developers with whom you'll have the opportunity to collaborate and are resourceful, take initiative and generate innovative solutions, there is no doubt that this is exactly where you need to be.




You'll be responsible for:

Working as either a Front-End, Back-End of Full-Stack developer;
Producing maintainable code that respects established standards and best practices;
Writing unit and integration tests for your work;
Actively participating in peer reviews;
Taking part in our Agile process by participating in SCRUM ceremonies;
Implementing fixes for and improvements to existing features;
Staying up to date on technologies and industry best practices;
Contributing to the continuous improvement of your team and the engineering department.




What we want from you:

Bachelor's degree or college diploma (DEC) in Computer Science, Software Engineering or equivalent experience;
3+ years of experience as a Developer;
Front-End: ReactJS, Bootstrap;
Back-End: C# and ASP.NET;
Knowledge of SQL and SQL Server;
Knowledge of ORMs (i.e. NHibernate), an asset;
Communication skills;
Ability to work as part of a team;
Functional English/French.




What you’ll get from us:

Competitive salary & insurance package;
Collective RRSP;
Wellness credit (500$ per year);
Amilia fitness classes (Yoga and Bootcamp);
Possibility to work from home, come to the office, or do a mix of both;
A strong work-life balance with paid vacation, personal days, and mini-Fridays;
Team-bonding and social activities once a quarter;
Up to 15 hours of group volunteering paid per year;
In-office snacks, including fresh fruit baskets, coffee, and free drinks;
Skill development opportunities through Lunch & Learn talks and company-wide Innovation Day.




About Amilia:

Amilia is more than just a tech company – we’re a close-knit family made up of caring, entrepreneurial-minded individuals. Our multi-disciplinary team members will challenge and support you on every project. We provide online registration and digital management software solutions to recreation organizations, such as gymnastics clubs, municipalities, sports centers, and many more.




We provide all our team members with the tools and flexibility they need to succeed every day. We also put an emphasis on collaboration and encourage everyone to bring new ideas to the table, even if it’s outside of your department. We’re not just here to sell software – we want to revolutionize the way recreation organizations leverage technology. Every Amilian is incredibly invested in our mission to disrupt the status quo and help our clients achieve great things.

